// Man page for mkdir
manMkdir="MKDIR(1)                         X Shell Manual                         MKDIR(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    mkdir - used to create folders
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>mkdir</b> [<b>-y</b>] <b>NAME</b>
    <b>mkdir </b><b>-l</b> [<b>-p</b> [<b>FULL_PATH</b>]] <b>NAME NAME NAME...</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Create directories on remote systems. Use -y to overwrite existing.
    Use -l for multiple directories with optional path specification.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>-y</b>
    Overwrite if exists
    Force directory creation

    <b>-l</b>
    Create multiple directories
    Space-separated names

    <b>-p PATH</b>
    Target directory
    Use with -l flag
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Single Directory</color>
    <b>mkdir NewFolder</b>
    Create in cwd

    <b>mkdir /home/tux/NewFolder</b>
    Create at path

    <color=#e4ff34># Multiple Directories</color>
    <b>mkdir NewFolder1 NewFolder2 NewFolder3</b>
    Create multiple

    <b>mkdir -l -p /home/tux dir1 dir2 dir3</b>
    Create in /home/tux

    <color=#e4ff34># Overwrite Mode</color>
    <b>mkdir -y existing</b>
    Force overwrite
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>mkcd</b>, <b>touch</b>"